args:
The prince and his friends' determination is
unshaken, even in the face of Tartarus warning
that they face annihilation at the Sacred Tree.
As the group makes for the tree, Gatov thinks
on two words Finlorda said: ＂The Progenitor.＂
Okay, what's up? He get bored of trying\nto murder us all of a sudden?
Done already, tough guy? Or did ya just\nrealize ya don't have the stones to back\nup the crap comin' outta yer mouth?!
Idiocy. Your way of fighting is paltrier still\nthan the romping of children; you hold no\nvalue as offerings to my king.
I pray you now see the fruitlessness of\nblind obedience to this doll, Cleo.
You delude yourself. Perhaps this is\nborn of your despair at losing our king.
It is nothing of the sort!
The prince is supported by uncountable\nallies and friends.
A king has no cause to surround himself\nwith an errant gaggle of lickspittles.\nA king is absolute, sui generis.
There are none who inherit\nHis Majesty's will.
Those who bore witness to his battles\nwere spellbound by his overwhelming wits\nand power—including his foes.
I leave you with a parting warning:\nGive yourself utterly to awaiting the\ndestruction of this world bereft of its king.
Should you venture to the Sacred Tree,\nyou will meet with ruin.
I swear my damn head's gonna explode\nfrom all the head-up-their-butt mumbo-\njumbo these guys keep spoutin' at us!
Yeah, don't listen to that dope, Cleo!
Of course I won't listen to him...
Cleo, I know that I'm nowhere near\nthe great man Alberius was.
But I have every intention of stepping up\nmy efforts in my own way.
I'll do it for everyone in this world,\nbut I'll also do it for me.
This delay was unfortunate, but we must\npress on. Whatever words may pass\nour duty remains unchanged.
Yes, we must hurry to the Sacred Tree.
(His Majesty's power was so overwhelming\nthat no amount of effort will ever allow\nsomeone to equal it.)
(And the prince is not even a legitimate\nson of the royal family, but instead a\nbeing born of the Other's flesh.)
(As someone who seeks to lead people\nto peace, this may be a great shackle\nupon him...)
King Jin, we've succeeded in bringing\ndown the Sacred Tree's barrier!
And with that, all is ready.
The seventh scion's group also makes\ntheir way to the Sacred Tree.
And it appears there is some\nother force approaching as well.
At long last, it begins...\nCome, Nedrick! Let us be off!
March forth, all of you! March forth and\nthrow wide the curtains on a new age\nfor all faeries!
(I will brook no failure now.\nThe Dawnshard WILL be mine.)
Guys, here! We should be able to see\nthe Sacred Tree in the distance soon!
Is something amiss, Gatov?\nYou seem a touch pensive.
Merely thinking about a conversation\nI had with Finlorda last night.
Is it true that the fifth scion of the Alberian\nroyal family absorbed the Other?
Unthinkable... Why, the Other had power\nenough to destroy an entire city a mere\nthousand years ago!
And what became of this fifth scion?
His current whereabouts are unknown,\nthough he is said to be in the company\nof the second scion, Phares.
We Faeries have encountered that name\nin various ancient documents and oral\ntraditions across the world.
You sound most troubled.\nIs it truly so great a threat?
I do not know. But looking at all of the\nunusual occurrences across the world\nthese days brought the name to mind.
(What is it that Finlorda sensed?\nAnd what is this ＂Progenitor＂?)
(We just don't have enough information.\nFor now, we'll simply have to focus on\ngetting to the Sacred Tree.)
(Your boy makes for the Sacred Tree,\nAurelius.)
(He seeks the thoughts you left behind\nfor him.)
